<HEADLINE>Drugs arrest at Eton</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975323139</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A MAN has been arrested on suspicion of drugs-related offences at Eton College.
Police were called to the school on Thursday evening, where they arrested a
19-year-old man.
A spokesman for Thames Valley Police last night confirmed that the man was in
custody at Slough being questioned over drugs-related offences at the school
where Prince William is a pupil. He refused to say whether the alleged offences
involved attempts to supply drugs to pupils at the #12,400-a-year Berkshire
public school or what drugs were allegedly involved.
No-one at Eton was available for comment last night.
There has been a series of drug scandals involving Eton boys this year.
In March, four were suspended after being arrested outside a London nightclub
on suspicion of having ecstasy, amphetamines, and cannabis.
Later that month, a 17-year-old was expelled after cannabis was found in his
traditional tail-coat.
In June, a boy was expelled for possessing cannabis and six others were
arrested outside the school on suspicion of having drugs.
</TEXT>
