<HEADLINE>Death of a park</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975323163</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
IT is one thing for Anne Evans to tell all us firework people to go to the park
(Death of a dog, November 14), but you can well imagine my face when I returned
not to a Roman Candle but a Fido Pooh in my garden on November 5.
Surely people who love dogs should love our environment which extends to nice
green, not brown, grass.
William C Watson,
2 Kenmar Gardens,
Uddingston.
</TEXT>
