<HEADLINE>`Drug squad' for disgraced soldiers</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975323166</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE 22 Argyll and Sutherland Highlanders who failed an Army drugs test face
being moved into a special platoon.
The plan would protect them from the attention of soldier col- leagues who
believe they have brought the regiment into disrepute, said an Army
spokes-woman yesterday.
The soldiers will be kept on normal duties until their fate has been decided.
The results of tests on the 22 remains un-changed after a second round of
laboratory tests on members of the regiment, based at Redford Barracks in
Edinburgh.
</TEXT>
