<HEADLINE>Stormin' success?</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>31</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975323277</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
HIGHLAND LEAGUE
CLACH, who play Elgin today, have won the race to sign striker Norman
MacMillan.
They are believed to have payed Caledonian Thistle #5000 for the youngster,
nicknamed Stormin' Norman because of his pace.
Forres travel to play Wick Academy, who are adopting an air of invincibility on
their home territory.
Recent form has pushed the club into seventh place in the league, and none of
their rivals relish the long trip north.
In contrast, Forres are propping up the table with Nairn on six points. With
County entertaining Huntly little change can be expected.
Cove Rangers must overcome on-form Deveronvale, while Keith, beaten Qualifying
Cup finalists, face Lossiemouth with both teams tied in fourth place on 20
points. Peterhead will stay third if they can beat Buckie Thistle away from
home.
</TEXT>
