<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>2</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975323282</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A builder appeared in court yesterday accused of starting a  #280,000 blaze at
a soccer ground.
Mr Derek Arthur Lacey, 32, of Staddiscombe, Plymouth, is charged with arson at
the Sportsman's Club at Hereford United's Edgar Street ground. He faces a
further charge of conspiracy to defraud and was remanded in custody for a week.
</TEXT>
