n WITHOUT a doubt it's an RAC ET phone home emergency mobile phone. I do quite
a bit of driving on my own and I used to drive quite an old Volvo with a dodgy
carburettor, so it's been invaluable. It has a special RAC button that puts you
right through and a 999 button for other emergencies. For someone like me who
drives to Bracknell where the Met Office is based and who has broken down more
than once , it's the most valuable thing I've ever bought.
n THIS was a train ticket in Sri Lanka which turned out to be the nightmare
trip of my life. There were hundreds of people in the train, on top of the
train, and holding on to the train. It took two hours of standing in
temperatures of 110 degrees with no air-conditioning. I have never been so hot
in my life because with so many people the temperature seemed to soar even
higher. I've still got the ticket as a memento.
