<HEADLINE>New-look All Blacks</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>30</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975323288</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
NEW Zealand have named a new-look team as they attempt to avoid a fourth
consecutive defeat against France in today's second Test at the Parc des
Princes.
France, who won a Test series 2-0 in New Zealand last year, retained the side
which won last Saturday's first Test 22-15 in Toulouse.
All Blacks coach Laurie Mains has made three changes and called up two uncapped
players, flanker Liam Barry and scrum half Justin Marshall, while Jeff Wilson,
who is suffering with a shoulder injury, gives up his full-back berth to Glen
Osborne.
French coach Jean-Claude Skrela is expecting a fierce battle from the All
Blacks. ``They'll want to prove that they are still a great side,'' he said.
All Blacks captain Sean Fitzpatrick admitted: ``That first Test was a real
disappointment. France played great rugby but we certainly didn't. We want to
prove that we can do much better. We want a win and we want it badly.''
</TEXT>
