<PAGE>43</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975323293</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
n HANK WANGFORD, country and western singer/gynaecologist
THIS is the holiday I'm on at the moment before I come over to Glasgow. On the
left edge of Europe I have a house perched on Connemara's seashore. I sit and
watch the sea breathe as tides come and go. My mother was from Govan and I've
always felt at home crossing Rannoch Moor and rolling down into Glencoe. So why
the west of Ireland? Well, Connemara is like Skye - bogs, no trees, mountains
and space - but with good craic.
</TEXT>
