<HEADLINE>Noorlander is top in baseline battle TENNIS</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>30</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975323295</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SAMANTHA Smith's impressive run in the Texaco Challenger event in Edinburgh
ended yesterday, when she lost in straight sets to Seda Noorlander in the last
four, writes Judy Murray.
Smith broke serve in the second game, but after failing to convert three break
points in the fourth, she won just seven more points as the sixth seed pocketed
the first set 6-2.
In the second set, Smith could not disrupt her opponent's relentless baseline
driving and was frequently caught out by some spectacular angles as the Dutch
player went on to take the set 6-4.
In today's final, Noorlander's opponent will be Russian teenager Julia Lutrova,
who outlasted Marion Maruska, of Austria, 7-6, 3-6, 6-2.
q.BORIS Becker needed the benefit of some complex mathematics to secure his
passage to the semi-finals of the ATP Tour World championship in Frankfurt.
Becker, who beat Russian Yevgeny Kafelnikov 6-4, 7-5 yesterday, finished with
the same record of two matches won and one lost in his section as American Pete
Sampras and South African Wayne Ferreira. But Ferreira was edged out because he
had the marginally weakest record of sets won and lost.
Sampras now meets Michael Chang while Becker takes on Sweden's Thomas Enqvist.
</TEXT>
