2-1 lead against Jersey's Val Stead, losing in five sets.
The other Scottish win came in the men's singles, where Graham Robertson edged
Jersey's David Le Marquand in a five-setter that ended on the
three-and-three-quarter-hour time rule, with the Scot 3-2 up in the decider.
