<DATE>951118</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Dolls  on  heels</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>JOHN DAVIDSON</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>26</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975323419</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Her boyfriend is a total dummy. Her I.Q. is even lower than her hip
measurement. And her days are spent posing at the mirror of a garish pink
plastic beauty salon. Who is that girl? No, not a supermodel - although the
similarities are striking - but Barbie, the dazzling superdoll star of our
kinky boot special.
So what makes a boot kinky? Answer: an overactive imagination. Knee-high boots
have too long been lodged in the fashion imagination as regulation footwear for
good-time girls.......girls such as Shirley Maclaine's tart-with-a-heart
character in Sweet Charity. For, in comparison with the fetishistic bondage
gear which has strutted down designer runways over recent years in the guise of
high fashion, don't knee-high boots seem positively demure?
As, at heart, is Barbie. She may bear an uncanny resemblance to the hooker from
hell. But don't be misled by that tousled mane of blonde hair, those dangly
earrings, or her perilously short skirts. She is a thoroughly respectable,
all-American (er, well. . . Malaysian-made) 36-year-old doll.
It's true that she is more brainless than the dizziest bimbo, but at least
Barbie knows a thing or two about fashion. And that is why she has made the
so-called kinky boot her footwear choice for the season.
For such a boot is suddenly the must-have fashion choice for a rather different
type of working girl - the type who may be running a personnel department
rather than a call-girl racket. It is the perfect partner for all those
knee-grazing sleeveless shifts which are fashion's latest contribution to the
executive wardrobe.
So throw away your those power-heeled courts. Sling your stilettos. And forget
those comfy pumps. If you want to get ahead in business, first get the boot.
Merchandising: JOHN DAVIDSON
Model: Barbie
All clothes: Model's own
</TEXT>
